{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential string truncation in _IdleMode_plmn_str function\n\n### Summary\nThe `_IdleMode_plmn_str` function in the EMM Idle Mode module may produce incorrectly null-terminated PLMN string representations when all digit fields in the input `plmn_t` structure are set to the invalid marker value (0x0F). This can lead to buffer over-reads or garbage output when the resulting string is used in subsequent network selection procedures or logging functions.\n\nThe issue manifests when the UE receives a PLMN identity where all MCC/MNC digits are marked as invalid. In such cases, the function would return without explicitly null-terminating the output buffer, potentially causing downstream functions to process uninitialized memory contents as valid PLMN identifiers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/IdleMode.c`: Added explicit null termination at the end of string construction to ensure proper C-string formatting even when no digits are written.\n"
}